<div class="fr-view Kanit panel-content-htmleditor"><p>CAM-ADV is an enhanced version of CADmeister/CAM. Due to add-on functions such as of preliminary machining, Preparation Settings, and high feed cutting radius end mills, it is capable of previously editing machining regions, checking the scope of machining, and efficiently performing rough machining (and intermediate-stage machining). Furthermore, CAM-ADV enables users to optimize the sequence of machining and create work flows without waste and re-working.</p><p><br></p><h2 class="fr-text-bordered">Features</h2><h3>Settings for Preparation</h3><hr><p>The Settings for Preparation (&#39;Work Settings&#39;) enables preliminary settings of machine tools of use, machining origin, table position, and so on. The scope of machining and the usability of angle-adjusting accessories (Attachments) can be checked, provided that a position of material and the information of machine have been input. Furthermore, it enables machining conditions to be automatically set for individual machines.<br><br></p><ul><li>Check of Machining Scope<br><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/8563D9D2-4CCB-BAA7-0A57-1BF0D72E4F02.jpeg" alt="Settings for Preparation" width="520" height="460" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Machining Patterns through the use of High Feed Cutting Radius End Mills</h3><hr><p>High-speed rough machining is enabled through the use of high feed cutting radius end mills. Furthermore, any portions of corners or gentle slopes that have been left uncut by the rough machining can be efficiently machined.<br><br></p><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/D307B290-457A-1362-BAF9-AD4B7877DC83.jpeg" alt="Settings for Preparation" width="520" height="350" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><h3 align="center"><br></h3><h3>Finishing Machining through the use of Preparatory Function</h3><hr><p>Subject areas for machining can be automatically divided in accordance with the extension length of tool blade. If any areas cannot be machined through the use of vertical axis, a rotational angle for tool operation can be automatically decided without causing interference around an angle adjusting accessory.<br><br></p><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/99608F9B-43AC-7BC9-98CD-16D4B82D582D.jpeg" alt="Settings for Preparation" width="520" height="470" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><p align="center"><br></p><h3>Improved Machining for Corners</h3><hr><p>Subject areas for machining can be automatically divided in accordance with the extension length of tool blade. If any areas cannot be machined through the use of vertical axis, a rotational angle for tool operation can be automatically decided without causing interference around an angle adjusting accessory.<br><br></p><p align="center"><img src="/uelthai/_content_html_editor_upload/images/E2697391-EFE6-4548-23A8-D9429DBB7A25.jpeg" alt="Improved Machining for Corners" width="520" height="440" class="fr-fic fr-dii"></p><h3>&nbsp;</h3><p><br></p><h3 class="fr-text-bordered">Inquiries</h3><p>If you have any inquiries about our product or would like to request a visit to your place for explanation or demonstration, please use the inquiry form.</p><p style="margin-left: 20px;"><a href="https://uelthai.co.th/contact"><span style="color: rgb(226, 80, 65);">Contact Us &rarr;</span></a></p></div><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a href="https://www.froala.com/wysiwyg-editor?pb=1" title="Froala Editor">Froala Editor</a></p><p data-f-id="pbf" style="text-align: center; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 30px; opacity: 0.65; font-family: sans-serif;">Powered by <a